Project Goals

The primary goal of this project is to create an engaging and informative fan website for Mohamed Salah, allowing visitors to:

Learn about Salah's life and career.

Explore his achievements and records.

View a gallery of iconic moments.

Interact through a contact form.

This project is designed as a practical exercise to demonstrate proficiency in HTML and CSS as part of the Code Institute curriculum.

Features

Current Features

Homepage: An overview of Mohamed Salah's significance and career highlights.

Biography Page: Detailed insights into Salah's early life, career journey, and personal achievements.

Achievements Page: A summary of major milestones and awards.

Records Page: A collection of significant records set or broken by Salah.

Gallery Page: A visually appealing grid of images showcasing Salah's career moments.

Contact Page: A simple form allowing users to send messages or inquiries.

Future Features

Integration of JavaScript for dynamic interactivity.

Addition of a blog section for news and updates about Salah.

Lightbox functionality for viewing images in the gallery.

Technologies Used

HTML5: Structuring the content of the website.

CSS3: Styling the website for visual appeal and responsive design.

Git and GitHub: Version control and project hosting.

